Hackathon is tomorrow!! Here are some details:
- Hackathon is 9am-8pm. I don't expect you to be there the whole time; if you need to pop out to take a break or go to a meeting or something, that's totally fine. But I want you to make an effort to work on a project or learn a skill different from what you normally do. The hope is that this is interesting enough to make you want to stay the whole time.
- Hackathon is at the TechArb workspace in town. Here's how to get there: If you google it, you'll see that TechArb is on Liberty, halfway between State and Division. If you come in off of Liberty, enter under the FedEx sign, turn right, and either take the elevators or go through two double doors to get to the stairs, then go down one floor and walk down the hall, it's just past the bathrooms. You can also enter from Washington St. When you walk in the door, turn around to get to the elevator/stairs, go down one floor, then it's just down the hall.
- KTP will be providing lunch (Jimmy Johns) and dinner (pizza) and we also have coffee and some fruits (bananas, apples)
- The <#CLG09G9DL|hackathon> channel will be your friend during before and during the event. If you have questions now, use it! During, you can use it to get help, get teammates, and share your project
- The post-hackathon party will be at Andrew Bunt's house (720 Arbor St) at 9pm. We have jungle juice, beer, pong, good vibes. Excellent way to relax after the hackathon!
I'm excited to tech out with you all tomorrow!
